name: KeyManagementException
comment:
This is the general key management exception for all operations dealing with key management. Examples of subclasses of KeyManagementException that developers might create for giving more detailed information could include:
  • KeyIDConflictException
  • KeyAuthorizationFailureException
  • ExpiredKeyException

constructors.name: KeyManagementException
constructors.comment:
Constructs a KeyManagementException with no detail message. A
 detail message is a String that describes this particular
 exception.

constructors.name: KeyManagementException
constructors.comment:
Constructs a KeyManagementException with the specified detail
 message. A detail message is a String that describes this
 particular exception.

constructors.name: KeyManagementException
constructors.comment:
Creates a {@code KeyManagementException} with the specified
 detail message and cause.

constructors.name: KeyManagementException
constructors.comment:
Creates a {@code KeyManagementException} with the specified cause
 and a detail message of {@code (cause==null ? null : cause.toString())}
 (which typically contains the class and detail message of
 {@code cause}).
